    <title type="html"><![CDATA[There can be only one css stylesheet per media]]></title>
    <link href="http://philippe.bourgau.net/there-can-be-only-one-css-stylesheet-per-medi/"/>
    <updated>2011-09-21T00:00:00+02:00</updated>
    <id>http://philippe.bourgau.net/there-can-be-only-one-css-stylesheet-per-medi</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>I thought it was a good idea to specify a media in my stylesheet link :</p>

<p><code>html
&lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="http://philippe.bourgau.net/stylesheets/tags.css" type="text/css" name="tags stylesheet" media="screen" /&gt;
</code></p>

<p>but when I tried to add another stylesheet, it was ignored !</p>

<p>```html</p>

<p><link rel="stylesheet" href="http://philippe.bourgau.net/stylesheets/common.css" type="text/css" name="main stylesheet" media="screen" />
<link rel="stylesheet" href="http://philippe.bourgau.net/stylesheets/tags.css" type="text/css" name="tags stylesheet" media="screen" />
```</p>

<p>It worked by removing the media attribute. It seems that only one stylesheet per media is taken into account.</p>
